claim: Natural rights are those that are dependent on the laws or customs, whereas legal rights are outside of a given legal system.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Legal rights are those bestowed onto a person by a given legal system  (  i.e. , rights that can be modified , repealed , and restrained by human laws  )  .

claim: Natural rights are those that are dependent on the laws or customs, whereas legal rights are outside of a given legal system.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Natural rights are those that are not dependent on the laws or customs of any particular culture or government , and therefore universal and inalienable  (  i.e. , rights that can not be repealed or restrained by human laws  )  .
